-- Sumitomo Plans to Take 49.9 Percent Stake in French Solar-Energy Project
-- B y   T s u y o s h i   I n a j i m a
-- 2010-11-25T02:08:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-25/sumitomo-plans-to-take-49-9-percent-stake-in-french-solar-energy-project.html
Sumitomo Corp. plans to take a 49.9
percent stake in a French solar power project, the Japanese
trading company said in a statment. The 30-megawatt project in
Les Mees, southern France, will cost 110 million euros ($147
million), Sumitomo said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tsuyoshi Inajima in Tokyo at 
